# 8lee.ai Cursor Rules

`CLAUDE.md` is the canonical technical resource. Reference it first.

## Documentation Hierarchy

- `CLAUDE.md` - Canonical workflow, coding, deploy, and privacy policy.
- `AGENTS.md` - Concise external-agent quick start.
- `README.md` - Public overview and setup.
- `docs/00-todos.md` - Active TODOs and future work. This is the only backlog file.
- `docs/01-privacy-indexing.md` - Noindex, crawler, and metadata policy.
- `app/demos/_docs/00-demos-readme.md` - Demo isolation guide.

## Quick Reference

- Runtime: Bun `1.3.13+`; do not add npm, yarn, or pnpm lockfiles.
- Quality check: `bun run check:full`.
- Styling: Tailwind-first; app-level theme/composition CSS belongs in `app/globals.css`.
- Testing: focus on command behavior, security/privacy headers, routing, and user-visible flows.
- Deployment: Vercel with `--scope death-note`.

## Core Principles

- Prefer simple solutions using existing patterns.
- Avoid duplicated docs, backlog files, and workflow instructions.
- Preserve the public-but-non-indexable posture for every metadata, route, middleware, asset, or deploy change.
- Use git history for completed work; keep `docs/00-todos.md` active-only.
